I have been playing Final Fantasy 14 a lot lately. I've barely scratched the surface of the lore and stories.
I have completed one expansion - A Realm Reborn - and have picked up all of the healer jobs I can, a couple of the damage jobs and all of the crafting jobs.

My social experience has been mostly good, a stark contrast to my experience playing World of Warcraft. I think the age range is slightly higher than WoW so the maturity level is significantly different.

I started playing as I got the gamer itch. I burned out from indie web stuff and needed something to engage my brain in the evenings. My best pal already played so I had someone to show me the ropes and play with.

I have been running a lot of dungeons, or 'duties' and made a bunch of internet friends already.

One person has offered hours of their personal time to boost me and my bestie through old (ARR) trials to get the special blue glowy horse mount, in exchange for lols and bants.

There are plenty of social activities set up by the community, one of my favourites are Bard concerts. The Bard job gets access to a plethora of instruments, and people have insane set ups with multiple characters and have them all in sync to play real life songs in-game. They draw a huge crowd and it's like a mini-party.

Another favourite is, again music based, clubs. And not the lewd kind (some are heavy on the ERP), but the sort where you just go to a chill venue on a Sunday night to listen to someone streaming their DJ set on Twitch. The concept is a bit wild, but is genuinely very fun. When I have a free Sunday evening, I like to pop to [Solstice](https://www.partake.gg/teams/381).

I've got a really, really long way to go to get to end game content. And I'm not sure what I'll do when I get there, but I enjoy healing, a lot, a lot. So maybe I'll join a static (group) to do end game content one day.
